 be modelled as originating from an orbital motion with\na period of 4.2 yr around an unseen companion with mass between 0.48 and 1\nMsun. The jet mass loss rate Mloss was derived from the OI luminosity and is in\nthe range 1E-8 and 1E-6 Msun/yr. This is the first direct Mloss measurement\nfrom a jet in a FUor. If we assume previous Macc estimates obtained through\nmodelling of the accretion disk, the derived range of Mloss would imply a very\nlow mass-ejection efficiency (Mloss/Macc < 0.02), which is lower than that\ntypical of T Tauri stars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 29 Aug 2016 09:58:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-28"}
